    "body": "I think this whole EIP has the wrong approach. You should NEVER trust a dapp to tell you what the transaction does. The client/wallet should always be the one trying to show the user the intended action, preferably using rad spec pulled from the contract (a lot of them publish already meta information to swarm, but nobody uses it yet) and if no info is available the client/wallet should provide it.",
